{"to":["sarah@email.com"],"subject":"Re: Neighborhood Recommendations Needed","body":"Hi Sarah,

Great to hear from you! I’m glad to help you get a feel for the area. Below are three neighborhoods that consistently stand out when friends ask for suggestions:

• Pinecrest – Excellent public schools, lots of green space, and well-maintained parks. Home prices are on the higher end, but many families feel the safety and amenities justify the cost.

• Oakwood – A more budget-friendly option that still offers a strong community vibe. The weekly farmers market and frequent local events give the neighborhood a welcoming, small-town feel.

• Riverdale – Closer to downtown with a lively mix of shops and restaurants. It’s ideal if you’d like an urban atmosphere while still having access to family-oriented spots like playgrounds and community centers.

Every neighborhood has its own character, so I recommend spending an afternoon in each to see which feels right for you. If you narrow your search or have specific questions (commute time, school zoning, etc.), let me know and I’ll dig up more details.

Hope this helps, and good luck with your home hunt!

Best,
John","cc":null,"bcc":null,"execution_log_path":"data/logs/item154_execution_log.json","card_path":"data/agent_cards/main154_sender.json"}
